HEADWORD: Starvedly
<hw>Starv"ed*ly</hw> <pr>(st⟦aum⟧rv"⟦ecr⟧d*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<def>In the condition of one starved or starving;
parsimoniously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some boasting housekeeper which keepth open doors for one day, . .
